I believe what you are saying is that you are trying to create a list with values from `x` to `y` so in your case, `1980` to `2014`. And you don&#39;t want to have to individually add each one, i.e.

```
list.add(1980);
list.add(1981);
list.add(1982);
...
```
What you can do is create an `IntStream` for a range of values and then add all of them to the list.

Like this,
```
List&lt;Integer&gt; years = IntStream.rangeClosed(1980, 2014).boxed().toList();
```

Note: `IntStream.rangeClosed(x, y)` will be inclusive to upper and lower bounds, meaning it will include all values from `x` to `y`, including `x` and `y`.

